-- Deutsche Telekom, UBS, Xstrata: European Equity Preview
-- B y   W h i t n e y   K i s l i n g
-- 2012-02-16T05:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-15/deutsche-telekom-ubs-xstrata-european-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
be active in  European (SXXP)  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  The  Stoxx Europe 600 Index  advanced 0.6 percent to 264.16.
The  Stoxx 50 Index  rose 0.3 percent to 2,492.25. The  Euro Stoxx
50 Index (SX5E) , a benchmark measure for nations using the euro,
climbed 0.2 percent to 2,493.96.  Deutsche Telekom AG (DTE)  (DTE GY):  Germany ’s largest telephone
company is evaluating options for an exit from the U.K. as it
seeks to raise cash after failing to sell its T-Mobile USA unit,
people with knowledge of the matter said. The stock fell 0.3
percent to 8.92 euros.  Tetragon Financial Group Ltd. (TFG)  : Officers and
directors of the investment firm that buys collateralized loan
obligations won dismissal of an investor’s lawsuit claiming they
used an “abusive scheme” to profit at the company’s expense.
The shares gained 2.2 percent to $6.85.  UBS AG (UBSN)  :  Switzerland ’s biggest bank sought
immunity from prosecution by Canadian regulators probing a
potential conspiracy to rig the price of derivatives worldwide,
three people with knowledge of the inquiry said. The shares
advanced 0.8 percent to 13 Swiss francs.  Xstrata Plc (XTA)  : The world’s largest exporter of
thermal coal is seeking a waiver on terms of a $6 billion loan
to allow it to remain in place for the duration of its proposed
merger with Glencore International Plc. The stock fell 0.4
percent to 1,179.5 pence.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Whitney Kisling in New York at 
 wkisling@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Rummer at   arummer@bloomberg.net  